已知信息：
'管理药品监管活动的全部范围的国家机构，根据国家药品立法至少包括以下所有职能:■新产品和现有产品的上市许可;
■质量控制实验室检测;
■药物不良反应监测;
■提供药品信息，促进合理用药;
■对制造商、批发商和分销渠道进行良好生产规范(GMP)检查和许可;
■执行操作;
■监测药物使用情况。'可被翻译为：A national body that administers the full spectrum of medicine regulatory activities, including at least all of the following functions in conformity with national medicine legislation:■marketing authorization of new products and variations of existing products;
■quality control laboratory testing;
■monitoring of adverse drug reactions;
■provision of information on medicines and promotion of rational use of medicines;
■good manufacturing practice (GMP) inspections and licensing of manufacturers, wholesalers and distribution channels;
■enforcement operations;
■monitoring of drug utilization.
'1.负责医疗产品上市许可和其他监管活动的国家机构。
2.在某一特定国家有权控制医疗产品进口和分销的管理机构。另见监管机构。'可被翻译为：1.The national agency responsible for the marketing authorization of, and other regulatory activities concerning, medical products.
2.A regulatory body with authority in a specific country to control the importation and distribution of medical products. See also regulatory authority.
'由国家监管机构认可的主管监管机构对文件证据的评估，以证明符合所需的良好规范(良好生产规范(GMP)、良好实验室规范和良好临床规范)，以支持上市许可和其他监管决定。案头评估可用于支持新的上市许可，或用于常规GMP检查(包括在所要求的指定产品生命周期管理框架内)。'可被翻译为：The evaluation of documentary evidence by a competent regulatory authority recognized by the national regulatory authority, for compliance with the required good practices (good manufacturing practices (GMP), good laboratory practices and good clinical practices) in support of marketing authorization and other regulatory decisions. Desk assessment may be performed in support of a new marketing authorization, or for routine GMP inspection (including in the frame of specified product(s) life-cycle management as required).
'1.质量管理的一部分，确保产品始终按照适合其预期用途的质量标准生产和控制，并符合上市许可、临床试验许可或产品规范的要求。GMP涉及生产和质量控制。GMP的主要目的是管理和尽量减少药品生产中固有的风险，以确保产品的质量、安全性和有效性。
2.质量保证的一部分，确保药品的生产和控制始终符合其预期用途和上市许可要求的质量标准。'可被翻译为：1.That part of quality management which ensures that products are consistently produced and controlled according to the quality standards appropriate to their intended use and as required by the marketing authorization, clinical trial authorization or product specification. GMP are concerned with both production and quality control. GMP are aimed primarily at managing and minimizing the risks inherent in pharmaceutical manufacture to ensure the quality, safety and efficacy of products.
2.That part of quality assurance that ensures that pharmaceutical products are consistently produced and controlled to the quality standards appropriate to their intended use and as required by the marketing authorization.

根据上述已知信息，请将'1.药监局:由成员国政府指定的管理药品在该国上市许可的机构
2.负责药品注册和其他监管活动的国家机构。
3.药监局:管理包括药监局在内的所有药品管理活动的国家机构
至少符合国家药品立法的下列所有职能:
•新产品的上市许可和现有产品的变型;
•质量控制实验室检测;
•药物不良反应监测;
•提供药品信息，促进合理用药;
•良好生产规范(GMP)检查和对制造商、批发商的许可
以及分销渠道;
•执法行动;
•监测药物使用情况。'翻译为英文，只能输出翻译后的句子，不允许添加编造成分。

